    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Employee Query Workflow Using Google Sheets\n\n## Overview\nThis workflow reads employee data from a **Google Sheet** and stores it in memory.  \nIt allows you to query the data using natural language and get intelligent responses.\n\n## How It Works\n1. The workflow connects to a **Google Sheet** containing employee data.  \n2. All records are loaded and stored in memory.  \n3. A user sends a query to the AI model.  \n4. The model processes the query against the stored data.  \n5. A structured and meaningful response is returned.\n\n## Example Queries\nYou can ask a wide range of questions, such as:\n- Get all employees  \n- List employees with a specific salary  \n- Group employees by gender and analyze salary  \n- Filter employees based on conditions  \n- Perform basic aggregations and insights  \n\n## What You’ll Learn\n- How to read data from **Google Sheets**  \n- How to store and manage data in memory  \n- How to query structured data using **natural language**  \n- How to build an AI-powered data assistant  \n\n## Output\nThe workflow returns:\n- Filtered employee lists  \n- Aggregated insights  \n- Structured responses based on your query  ",
